edu.umass.cs.benchlab.har

Class HarCustomFields

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.umass.cs.benchlab.har.HarCustomFields

  • public class HarCustomFields
extends java.lang.Object
    This class defines a HAR custom fields. From the specifications, each HAR file can contain custom fields. A custom field is made of a (name, value) string pair. Manipulating HarCustomFields in an object is done this way: 
     HarLog hl = new HarLog(config) ;
 //Add or set :
 hl.getCustomFields().addCustomField("name", "value");
 //Get :
 String value = hl.getCustomFields().getCustomFieldValue("name");
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Fabien Mottet
